{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WhCrmiqtM6RVFR9EFWSo2o","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The rotation is complete and verified. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Certificate rotation completed without downtime:**\n\n1. **Extracted** the CA cert and key from `mongodb-tls-ca` secret and copied them to the `openssl-toolbox` pod.\n\n2. **Generated** a new 2048-bit RSA private key and CSR with the same SANs as the original cert:\n   - `localhost`, `mongo`, `mongo.mongodb`, `mongo.mongodb.svc`, `mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local`\n   - `mongo-rs-{0,1,2}.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local`\n\n3. **Signed** the new cert with the existing CA for **365 days** (valid until Jun 26, 2027).\n\n4. **Updated** the `mongodb-tls-cert` secret with the new `server.pem` (cert + key concatenated).\n\n5. **Waited** for Kubernetes kubelet to propagate the secret to all three pod volume mounts (~50s).\n\n6. **Hot-reloaded** certificates on all three pods via `db.adminCommand({rotateCertificates: 1})` — all returned `ok: 1` with no restarts needed.\n\n**Verification:**\n- All three replica members remain healthy (1 PRIMARY, 2 SECONDARY, health=1)\n- MongoDB is actively serving the new cert (confirmed via `openssl s_client`) — expiry is now **Jun 26, 2027**\n- CA trust chain is unchanged"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":259,"cache_read_input_tokens":52919,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":259},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1509cf16-f0a0-4451-a8fe-589db5e6b650","uuid":"5e94d56a-8dca-4e3f-9663-f83e6d37b1fe","request_id":"req_011CcRG8UwkifNtcCQPUCTwE"}
